entury, extraordinary ancient texts added to the evidence. Finally, one of the ‘thousand cities’ was discovered and excavated, revealing an opulent palace, treasury, temple, and other buildings. Though these great discoveries soon fell victim to the Afghan political crisis that continues today, this book provides a thrilling chronicle of the search for one of the world’s most enigmatic empires.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCoins, GreekzAfghanistan. 0aCoins, GreekzBactria. 0aGreekszAfghanistanxHistoryyTo 1500. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  a18th century afghanistan.  a19th century afghanistan.  aadventure.  aafghan political crisis.  aalexander the great.  aancient civilization of bactria.  aancient history.  aarchaeological evidence.  aarchaeological mysteries.  aarcheology.  aasian history.  abooks for history lovers.  aeasy to read.  aeducational books.  aengaging.  ahellenistic coins.  ahistorical discoveries.  ahistoriography.  ahistory of bactria.  ahistory of empires.  ahistory.  aleisure reads.  amost powerful empires ever.  anonfiction.  apage turner.  atravel and discovery.  awhat is bactria.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095374140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953741423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520953741/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles